social_posts.post_text: Our lil big burst of sunshine ☀️✨🌴

So much fun doing our first sprint triathlon today. Having ACL reconstruction surgery when I was 16 and a few minor meniscus scopes, then retearing it again 6 years ago. I decided to opt out of surgery and strengthen my leg muscles to compensate. On Friday I saw the orthopedic surgeon and she explained the deterioration of meniscus. (arthritis) from years of sports and injuries but my muscles are strong and protecting my knees stability. The body is amazing. I am so grateful for its ability to heal, adapt, and to finish this race with my best friend.
🩵God created such a beautiful place for us to play🌴
Once upon a time in a Ginormous city with the @bodyglove crew, I felt very micro.
A few days before Koa Bearskie was born
@kyle_krause insisted we have the legend  @emeryphoto take maternity photos. So glad he did🥰

Partied hard all weekend till after midnight for lobster opener with the best crew! Each night we would start off with a 30-60ft scuba at Bird Rock and back to the mooring for another free dive around the shoreline. Going to bed around 1-2am. Probably the bravest thing I’ve learned to do and one of hardest sports to get comfortable and good at. Every time we descend I think, “This is absolutely nuts”, but after I think “That was so Rad.”Watching my brothers master the skill of Lobster Diving and learning from them is one of the most fun experiences we get to do together. Thank you @gregsworld and @bodyglove for teaching us your ways and giving the opportunity to learn this awesome Sport!
4 years old. The kindest, funny,fun, and loving son we could ever ask for. Love you so much Koa Bear 🩵
Mom and Dad go to Catalina. A little weather but a lot of fun 🐳

Clifford you were the most loyal and loving best friend I could ever ask for. You went everywhere with us and were so chill and fun. Our memories together and your spirit will live with us everyday till we get to the party in the clouds and see you again for more love and adventures. We love you to heaven and back. See you soon lil buddy 🩵
The ocean fills the heart 🩵, inspires the imagination 🌴and brings eternal joy ☀️to the soul

My last video part a lot of people might not have seen. @trevermaur got the crew from the west coast together and we filmed for a year. A few months in I tore my ACL at a contest. Knowing this was my last video part, I wanted to finish filming throughout the year, opted out of surgery, and strengthened my legs as much as possible. I didn’t land all the tricks I wanted to but we had so much fun filming with the crew and the film came out awesome. The crew worked hard together making sure each part came out great and were at all the winch spots supporting each other. Full Dog Dayz film available on iTunes. Thank you @trevermaur and the crew for everything!
